title: Synthetix Ambassador Election 23/06/21
body:
### What is this election?
This snapshot election is to nominate 3 Synthetix Ambassadors to serve under the Synthetix Ambassador Program.

Nominated Synthetix Ambassadors will be locked in for a 3-month Ambassador Epoch.

### What is the Synthetix Ambassador Program?
Synthetix Ambassadors enable community token holders to delegate their ERC-20 tokens from other projects (yCRV, BAL, UNI, etc) in order to participate in external protocol governance that benefits the Synthetix Ecosystem (liquidity incentives, synth listings, etc)

### Is this role paid?
The Synthetix DAO will allocate a monthly stipend to incentivise Synthetix Ambassadors to perform their external governance duties.

#### How are votes weighted?
To vote in the election, SNX holders will need to have staked within the last fee period snapshot before the start of the Election Period. 

Each staking wallet will be able to vote for one nominee, and a wallet's vote weighting takes their staking debt at the relevant snapshot and multiplies it quadratically, as outlined in [SIP-90](https://sips.synthetix.io/sips/sip-90).

#### How to vote?
Choose an option below.

To help match the wallet address with the nominee identity visit the spreadsheet [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nbAUAioVvxlhtBzUI0dwmedGC2R3AZL-mDws7BzvZDQ/edit?usp=sharing)
